<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" ?>
<ContentPage xmlns="http://xamarin.com/schemas/2014/forms"
             xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml"
             x:Class="IntStd1.Views.EssentialsPage"
             Title="Essentials">
    <ContentPage.Content>
        <!--<StackLayout>
            <Label Text="Welcome to Essentials Page!"
                VerticalOptions="CenterAndExpand" 
                HorizontalOptions="CenterAndExpand" />
        </StackLayout>-->

        <ScrollView>
            <StackLayout Padding="10" Spacing="10">
                <Frame BorderColor="Teal" Padding="5" HasShadow="True">
                    <StackLayout Orientation="Vertical">
                        <Label Text="Get a SIM Card" FontAttributes="Bold" FontSize="Medium"/>
                        
                        <Image Source="sim" 
                               Aspect="AspectFit"                                
                               HorizontalOptions="FillAndExpand" 
                               VerticalOptions="StartAndExpand">
                            
                        </Image>

                        <Label Text="SIM card is the first thing you want to buy so that you can start calling and texting your friends. This also let's you 
have internet connection on the go so you won't lost in the middle of nowhere. There are many SIM providers in Australia, 
for e.g. Vodafone, Optus, Telstra etc. Go online and search which provider will suit you as they have different plans.
Find the best plan and even add a phone into it if you current phone is not so smart." 
                                LineBreakMode="WordWrap"
                                HorizontalOptions="FillAndExpand"
                               FontSize="Small" />
                    </StackLayout>
                </Frame>
                
                <Frame BorderColor="Teal" Padding="5" HasShadow="True">
                    <StackLayout Orientation="Vertical">
                        <Label Text="Open a Bank Account" FontAttributes="Bold" FontSize="Medium"/>
                        <Image Source="bank" 
                               Aspect="AspectFit"                                
                               HorizontalOptions="FillAndExpand" 
                               VerticalOptions="StartAndExpand">

                        </Image>
                        <Label Text="
Open a bank account so you can deposit the cash/cheques you have brought from your home country. Signing up for a bank
account will help you to get a bank card so you can start paying through it. Make sure to choose the bank that has their Branches near to where you live
so that it will be easier to visit them when in trouble. Banks like Commonwealth, ST. George, ANZ are one of the leading bank here in Australia." 
                               LineBreakMode="WordWrap"
                               HorizontalOptions="FillAndExpand"
                               FontSize="Small" />
                    </StackLayout>
                </Frame>


                <Frame BorderColor="Teal" Padding="5" HasShadow="True">
                    <StackLayout Orientation="Vertical">
                        <Label Text="Buy a Transportation Card" FontAttributes="Bold" FontSize="Medium"/>
                        <Image Source="opal" 
                               Aspect="AspectFit"                                
                               HorizontalOptions="FillAndExpand" 
                               VerticalOptions="StartAndExpand">

                        </Image>
                        <Label Text="You will need to travel a lot, so you need to get a valid transportation card. There are different card in different state of Australia. Transportation card
in Sydney are called Opal whereas in Melbourne there is Myki. So buy a travel card from one of the nearest store and make sure to top up with plenty of funds in it
and don't forget to Tap On and Tap Off everytime you get on and off the train/bus." 
                               LineBreakMode="WordWrap"
                               HorizontalOptions="FillAndExpand"
                               FontSize="Small" />
                    </StackLayout>
                </Frame>



            </StackLayout>
        </ScrollView>
    </ContentPage.Content>
</ContentPage>